reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I like it
reviews.reviewText: It's a very nice feeling book, and the pages are cool. They are numbered, but I personally like that a lot. The blankness of the pages bring me immense joy

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It’s good. The paper is unlined, I enjoy that it is good for artistic expression. It got me back into journaling. Unlined, clean, still has some writing, but it is a good notebook.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality for its price
reviews.reviewText: I never thought such a cheap sketchbook could hold this much quality. The paper is not white but a cream color so keep that in mind. But the paper is really good for quick sketches and notes. I love mine so much I had to order again and now I own 6 of these babies.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars My favorites to use right now
reviews.reviewText: These are my favorite sketchbooks to use right now. I do half of my drawings on paper and the other digitally but i like all the space they give, soft but good paper material, and that the book itself is pretty low profile, its easy to fit in places. It doesnt have a crazy amount of pages for someone who may draw a lot everyday, but it does have a healthy amount of pages and they're even numbered. You can even draw on the cover(might want the tan version for that though), would use a pen for good measure. Only thing that makes it imperfect is that due to the design of thr stitching its hard to work on the back of the page because you cant get it to lay flat without the other side of the book falling on your hand. But thats obvious with this design.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 28, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars One of the best
reviews.reviewText: I'm super fussy about my notebooks, I have to take a lot of notes (I also use Rocketbooks for notes that require categorization and transcription). I like paper that when u write on it it doesn't impress on the sheet below or start to curl, also I like paper that doesn't blot when I use a fountain or marker-like pen, nor do I see the point of super fancy notebooks etc.. Hence, I use sketch books. But this is something I gave to a friend, he loves it, it checked all the right boxes, I liked it so much I got one for myself. A quality no-nonsense notebook for a banging price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Notebook, big with thick paper
reviews.reviewText: After writing in all these small notebooks, I feel like I'm in a palace with this notebook. The sheets are thick, my Precise V5 pen doesn't bleed through as it would for cheaper paper. The paper also holds on to my pen in a nice responsive way.My only concern is the binding. Might not be an issue though since the fold occurs around a centimeter off from the spine. I'll post an update later. I'm not a big fan of the font they used for the front, a minimalist blank cover would be nicer.Overall, I recommend the notebook. It's a great price for what you get and I've always wanted to have a larger blank notebook.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 22, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Came messed up :(
reviews.reviewText: I was very excited for this notebook, I thought it would be perfect for doodling and all. When I got it, there was a huge dent in it that makes it crooked. It’s hard to explain but I will attach pictures. The inside is nice, it has page numbers which I do like. The inside paper is more of the tan rather than a white. I do like this notebook, just wish mine didn’t come messed up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Will be buying again
reviews.reviewText: I bought this notebook to practice long calculus problems. The blank pages are great for calculations and my notes look neater. I write mostly in pencil with some underlining done in pen and don’t see much of it appear on the other side of the paper as others have mentioned. Regardless the notebook is so inexpensive in comparison to others I saw that I will just be using one leaf of each page anyway and then buy another when it is filled up. The material of the cover is nice and soft to the touch. I do wish however that it were a spiral notebook
The quality of the page is very good. Very smooth cover to touch. Feels very good to write on it.
Buon quaderno ma mancano alcune descrizioni, ovvero se le pagine sono a quadretti o a righe.Spoiler: sono completamente bianche.
Le pagine lasciano trapassato un po' il colore dei pennarelli a spirito, ma rimane comunque un ottimo articolo, lo ricomprerò sicuramente.

reviews.reviewTitle: Cute notebook but ink passes through!
reviews.reviewText: Cute notebook! I really like the feel of it, the cover and the pages are soft :) However, the paper is a little thin, so ink passes through onto the other side, and even ballpoint pens will leave a pressure mark on the next page. Overall still satisfied.
Re-ordered twice now and will again. Good quality and value for the money
